Banyana Banyana will face Zambia in the final of the Cosafa Women's Championship on Sunday. JOHANNESBURG - Banyana Banyana will face Zambia in the final of the Cosafa Women's Championship on Sunday. The defending champions brushed aside neighbours Zimbabwe 3-1 in Thursday's semi-final at the Wolfson Stadium in Port Elizabeth. Though concerned by the goal conceded, coach Desiree Ellis says the team continues to show signs of improvement. "I thought we were really good, we conceded poorly though," she said. Ellis said the execution was "absolutely magnificent".